BIRD flu has been found in swans and at two small poultry farms in the Czech Republic, Agriculture Minister Marian Jurecka said last week. State Veterinary Administration chief Zbynek Semerad said the highly contagious H5-type virus has been confirmed and further tests have been performed to determine whether it is the deadly N8 sub-type found.Two zones have been put in place around the areas at 3km and 10km. They are preparing to cull the infected poultry and other birds.The H5N8 strain has been recently detected in the neighbouring countries of Germany and Slovakia. &ndash; REUTERS